# Firebase And Backend Rules

## Runtime Expectations

- Preserve the current deployment shape and entrypoints unless the task explicitly changes infra.
- Keep function handlers straightforward and easy to trace.
- Avoid changing request and response payload contracts without updating all consumers.

## Safety

- Do not hardcode secrets or credentials.
- Keep environment-specific values configurable.
- Prefer explicit validation and helpful error messages for malformed input.

## Interop

- This repository appears to bridge frontend progress views with backend progress data.
- If backend payload shape changes are necessary, update frontend consumers in the same task and call out the contract change clearly.
